+\begin{theorem}[Operadic homotopy convolution theorem; \ClaimStatusProvedElsewhere{} {\cite{LV12,KontsevichSoibelman,Tamarkin00}}]
+\label{thm:operadic-homotopy-convolution}
+Let $C$ be a conilpotent dg cooperad and $P$ a dg operad.  There is a
+complete filtered $L_\infty$-algebra
+\[
+\operatorname{Conv}_{\infty}(C,P),
+\]
+well defined up to filtered $L_\infty$ quasi-isomorphism, with the
+following properties.
+\begin{enumerate}[label=\textup{(\roman*)}]
+\item Its Maurer--Cartan elements are precisely the
+  $\infty$-twisting morphisms from~$C$ to~$P$.
+\item An $\infty$-quasi-isomorphism in either variable induces an
+  $L_\infty$ quasi-isomorphism on the corresponding homotopy
+  convolution objects.
+\item If $C$ and $P$ are already strict models in which no higher
+  coherences have been resolved, then the classical convolution dg Lie
+  algebra $\Hom_{\mathbb{S}}(C,P)$ is a strictification of
+  $\operatorname{Conv}_{\infty}(C,P)$.
+\end{enumerate}
+For ordinary dg coalgebras and algebras this specializes to the pair
+$(C,A)$ and the strict dg Lie algebra $\Hom(C,A)$.
+\end{theorem}
+
+\begin{proof}[Explanation]
+The twisting-morphism formalism of~\cite{LV12} identifies homotopy
+$P$-algebra structures with square-zero coderivations on the cofree
+$C$-coalgebra.  The resulting deformation complex is complete and
+filtered by arity or bar length, and homotopy transfer transports it to
+any quasi-isomorphic model.  The homotopy classification of such
+deformation problems is naturally $L_\infty$-valued in the sense of
+Kontsevich--Soibelman; Tamarkin's enhancement of deformation complexes
+is the prototypical example showing that the strict dg Lie shadow need
+not be the whole story.
+\end{proof}
 
